data.title: Partnering for green steel production at scale, ROTOBOOST and Baowu, the world's largest steelmaker, collaborate under the BF-MOST Joint Innovation Call.
data.description: In Shanghai on October 31, 2025, ROTOBOOST of Finland and Baowu Clean Energy of China were revealed as the selected participants in the Business Finland (BF) – Ministry of Science and Technology of China (MOST) Joint Innovation Call. This initiative, backed by the governments of both countries, aims to foster collaboration between Finnish and Chinese entities.

data.title: AS Ekspress Grupp's revenue rises in Q3 & 9 months of 2025 due to investments in conference business, ticket sales, digital screens, and media subscriptions.
data.description: Throughout the third quarter and the initial nine months of the year, Ekspress Grupp observed a consistent increase in revenue, fueled by the Group's ventures into conference business, ticket sales, and digital outdoor screens. Furthermore, there was a notable uptick in digital subscriptions for media companies associated with the Group.

data.title: Coty releases FY25 Sustainability Report, focusing on eco-desirability and transparency. CEO Sue Nabi highlights progress.
data.description: Coty Inc. (NYSE: COTY) and Paris: COTY) unveiled its Fiscal Year 2025 (FY25) Sustainability Report, outlining advancements in creating a more sustainable beauty industry. Through its Beauty that Lasts plan, Coty reduced water usage, improved ingredient disclosure, and began partnerships with suppliers and retailers. CEO Sue Nabi stated, "Coty is dedicated to showcasing sustainability..."

data.title: Xi Jinping and Donald Trump discuss bilateral ties in Busan, South Korea. Xi ready to work with Trump.
data.description: In Busan, South Korea on October 31, 2025, Chinese President Xi Jinping and US President Donald Trump held discussions regarding bilateral relations and mutual interests. President Xi expressed readiness to further engage in dialogue with President Trump.

data.title: Talkmate launches AI-powered multilingual Chinese education agent for cultural exchange. Available in English, French, and Arabic.
data.description: In Beijing on October 31, 2025, Talkmate International Chinese Education is making cultural exchange easier by offering conversations with historical figures like Confucius and Li Bai in multiple languages such as English, French, and Arabic. This unique opportunity allows for discussions on philosophy and poetry while enjoying a morning coffee without any language barriers.
